Install
-------
sudo apt install libnss3-tools
curl -JLO "https://dl.filippo.io/mkcert/latest?for=linux/amd64"
chmod +x mkcert-v*-linux-amd64
sudo cp mkcert-v*-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/mkcert

Usage
-----
mkcert -cert-file cert.pem -key-file key.pem 0.0.0.0 localhost 127.0.0.1 ::1

mkcert kifarunix-demo.com '*.kifarunix-demo.com' localhost 127.0.0.1 ::1
Sample command output;
Created a new certificate valid for the following names üìú
 - "kifarunix-demo.com"
 - "*.kifarunix-demo.com"
 - "localhost"
 - "127.0.0.1"
 - "::1"

Reminder: X.509 wildcards only go one level deep, so this won't match a.b.kifarunix-demo.com ‚ÑπÔ∏è

The certificate is at "./kifarunix-demo.com+4.pem" and the key at "./kifarunix-demo.com+4-key.pem" ‚úÖ

It will expire on 31 August 2023
